<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF4AFF8A1D95FE709D5DFC95" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF4AFF8A1D95FE709D5DFC95" blockId="23.[151,1437,356,923]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4AFF8A1D95FE709974FD90" bold="true" box="[199,322,500,526]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized (TL: 
<quantity id="664DB6BCBF4AFF8A1F73FE709A9CFD91" box="[545,682,500,527]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.1" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="5.3" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="5.1">5.1–5.5 mm</quantity>
), oblong-oval species. Head reddish-brown, clypeus somewhat paler – testaceous; pronotum reddish-brown with broadly testaceous anterior margin and lateral sides; elytra dark brown, basal margin and especially lateral sides paler – testaceous. Pronotum with short longitudinal strioles laterally. Each elytron with six complete discal striae and one submarginal stria: all striae beginning at base and ending close to apex, only stria 6 shorter and ending at apical fourth; submarginal stria long, beginning at about elytral mid-length (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF4AFF8A1DF2FD2C98C1FD5D" box="[160,247,680,707]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[230,1356,193,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@37.[217,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Habitus of Copelatus in China. 25. C. weymarni (♂; Kaymanovka, Russia); 26. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype ♂; Xiniudong, Guizhou); 27. C. zimmermanni (♀; Danxia Shan, Guangdong); 28. C. sp. (♀; Lantau, Hongkong). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411114/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view sickle-shaped with apex slightly turned dorsally, with large irregular process on dorsal side near mid-length (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF4AFF8A1F9CFD489B12FD79" box="[718,804,716,743]" captionStart="FIGURES 63–70" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,200,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[205,1383,181,1379]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 63–70. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 63, 65, 67, 69. median lobe in lateral view; 64, 66, 68, 70. paramere. 63–64. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (holotype, Beihai, Yunnan); 65–66. C. weymarni (Honshu, Japan); 67–68. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype, Xiniudong, Guizhou); 69–70. C. zimmermanni (Danxiashan, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410764/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
). Parameres moderately broad, ‘C’-shaped; apex rather slender; apical lobe long, club-shaped (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF4AFF8A1F1CFD749A95FC95" box="[590,675,752,779]" captionStart="FIGURES 63–70" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,200,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[205,1383,181,1379]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 63–70. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 63, 65, 67, 69. median lobe in lateral view; 64, 66, 68, 70. paramere. 63–64. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (holotype, Beihai, Yunnan); 65–66. C. weymarni (Honshu, Japan); 67–68. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype, Xiniudong, Guizhou); 69–70. C. zimmermanni (Danxiashan, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410764/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
). Female similar to male, strioles on pronotum more numerous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF4AFF8A1D95FC9099CAFC05" pageId="23" pageNumber="274" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF4AFF8A1D95FC9099CAFC05" blockId="23.[151,1437,356,923]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF4AFF8A1D95FC909957FCB0" bold="true" box="[199,353,788,814]" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Distribution.</emphasis>
A species described from 
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF4AFF8A1FC5FC919B7FFCB0" box="[663,841,788,815]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
(not 
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF4AFF8A1ED9FC909C16FCB0" box="[907,1056,788,814]" country="China" name="Heilongjiang" pageId="23" pageNumber="274">Heilongjiang</collectingRegion>
